MADE BY: Xtra-Hoot (panic! at T spawn)

ROOMTACTIK_TEXTURE_B2 is a deathmatch map with multiple routes.  From the spawn players can either go towards the choke point which has been engineered so players cannot be shot coming out of spawn and to engage in combat have to move round the corner  to the enemy, they may also climb the walls of the spawn to  the middle platform which has ladders to another area below which then leads to the map floor.  Taking the other path from spawns, players reach the path at the back where the blocks make it difficult knowing where your enemy is.

NEW:  

Converted map to Texture from bricks
Added middle section
Added ladders in Spawns
Balanced sizes of walkways
Added ladders to lower platform and bottom

This map is based on Black Mesa, the research facility were Half Life takes place.
Everything in the map is pretty realistic. When you damage electronic panels they spark, if you shoot the lights, some break and turn off, glass windows break, etc. I've been testing it with NPCs and I found it really entertaining. It's a fairly large map. It's got a storage room, labs, offices, and a testing chamber. Very good map for a team deathmach based game. 

ALSO! FEEL FREE TO PUT THIS MAP ON A SERVER. I can't create one because my internet sucks right now.

Within the mysterious Equator Wall of this ancient world, the towers of the mythical, godlike Architects stand. This structure, the House of Solitary, is home to a particularly significant Architect by the name of Relative Solitary.

This map supports 32 players and has buyzones. It mainly consists of an open field surrounding the House of Solitary, and the central chamber of the House itself.

This map has been updated greatly. New sections have been added on so that it is now much less constrictive. The is able to be decompiled if anyone wishes to use this map for other types of game play. The map has also been greatly optimized to look much better. If you do not like the color correction in the map, just type "mat_colorcorrection 0" in console.


Note - any errors that occur as a result of decompiling is yours alone to sort out.

This is a remake of the map dm17 from Quake3 Arena. Custom textures, ingame music (guess what, music from Q3A) and of course many teleports. A must have for any Quake 3 lover. It is recommended that you play with 10 players max but it can support as many players as you want. Only for the Deathmatch plug-in. It won't work nice on standard servers. 

Note that there is a "haste" powerup like in Q3A.

Features: Custom Textures (let me know if you have issues with this *black & purple*)

that wall and inside.
Breakable wall near T spawn, next to a ladder.
*My favorite*: The breachable door at T spawn, you'll see it there as a wooden door. Shoot at/near the 
handle to break the door open to go inside. Otherwise it will not open. (Pretty cool right? ya.)

Bots do pretty well with the map, give it a try. (they love the big building)
